Description: Olympus Imported offer the highest quality parts, quality people, and quality service.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Olympus was founded in 1977 as Olympic Imported Parts Corp. Operating out of a small, single bay warehouse and showroom in Alexandria, Virginia, they were established as a full line imported car parts outlet for a much larger importer of German car parts. They sold and delivered parts to professional repair facilities, service stations and chains as well as the “do it yourself” walk-in customers. With seven employees and three delivery vehicles, even in the formative, early years, their focus was on providing professional and DIY mechanics the highest quality import parts available, pricing it right and getting it there fast!. In the fall of 1986, Michael Brown, then store manager, purchased the assets of Olympic Imported Parts Corp. of Virginia from the original owner, Karl Flicker. It was a scary time. The receivables of the company were about the same as the newly acquired debt service, so it was vital to keep overhead low and just go crazy growing the sales of the company. In those early days, everyone was responsible for everything: salesmen sold parts, posted inventory, pulled their own orders, and usually stayed until late at night restocking their inventory. They believed that whether they succeeded or not, no one was going to outwork us. Through the 1980s & 90’s, the import car market was growing at an exceptional rate and so was their company. Sales were increasing, their delivery fleet was expanding, as was the work required to keep up with their growth. Additional warehouse space was soon needed to house their ever-expanding inventory. What began as a small business with a handful of employees gradually became a fast growing, thriving enterprise. In fact, the Washington Business Journal in 1995 presented us with their “Fast Track” award for being among the fastest growing businesses in the Washington, D.C. area in the category of distribution. After 27 years, it was time get a fresh new look for their company and in 2004, they dressed up their company vehicles with their new “energy-laced” logo and changed their name from Olympic to Olympus Imported Auto Parts. It is not possible to travel the roads of the D.C. area without seeing their flashy and friendly Olympus Scion XB’s.

Description: Tipping Bucket is a crowd-sourced venture charity enabling catalytic capital and funding via media to non-profits, businesses, and startups.
Full Description: Tipping Bucket is a a crowd-sourced venture philanthropy platform. It helps non-profits, social businesses, and startup social entrepreneurs leverage social media to provide catalytic capital and fund projects that do social good.  The Tipping Bucket site launches one specific "Change the World" project at a time, in one of seven impact sectorsâ€” Community, Health, Education, Energy, Environment, Justice and Opportunity.  Each project has a specific funding goal and a deadline. Working alongside partners and collaborators, the site uses social media to guide micro-donors to each project to pledge as little as $1 (the default amount) to help that project get off the ground. While there is no limit to what donors can give, the model is to raise significant financial and social capital for these ventures by spreading world-changing ideas and examples through ever-widening networks of individual donors who each contribute relatively small donations.  Tipping Bucket's commitment to its donors is to "change the world or your money back." If the funding goal isn't met by the specific deadline, none of the transactions are processed and the next project gets its turn in the bucket.  Tipping Bucket is a 501(c)(3) non-profit corporation that strives to combine the best of business, philanthropy and social entrepreneurship into a new breed of non-profit.

Description: Miss O and Friends is a media and lifestyle brand that offers advice and support for girls.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Miss O and Friends is a cross-platform COPPA complaint, CARU certified, verified safe original media and lifestyle brand for tween girls. Our mission has always been help empower and build self-esteem in young girls by giving them a platform to express themselves, ask questions, get advice and have fun. Currently, we do this through our app, series, and website. Developed with a division of Sprint, the Girl2Girl Wall is a free, safe COPPA compliant socialization app geared toward tween and young teen girls. All submissions are screened by real people to ensure there is no identifiable information, bullying, hate language, swear words, and the content is appropriate for the tween girl community. Unlike other social media apps, there are no likes, followers or photos. Instead, the Girl2Girl Wall is a judgment free-zone where girls can get advice from other girls their age for IRL situations. Girls helping girls is really powerful, and by creating an environment where it’s cool to do that, just imagine how much good can come from it. We are also the creators of the YouTube Original series, Hyperlinked, which is inspired by the story of Miss O and Friends and follows 5 girls in middle school as they build a website to help other girls, while navigating middle school. The series has a heavy focus on STEM, coding, entrepreneurship and positive female friendships. To help build self-esteem, we create programs that allow girls to express themselves in a variety of different outlets. All of our web content is created by our girl community. We are truly by girls, for girls. Whether it's getting their own original stories published and sold, entering into a fashion design contest, or contributing content as a Miss O intern, we get girls involved as much as possible. The site also includes games, quizzes, blogging, advice, celebrity scoop, music and contests.
